    <summary>Synchronize Markdown documentation with Confluence</summary>
    <description>
ConSync is a command-line tool that synchronizes local Markdown documentation with Atlassian Confluence.

## Features

- **Markdown to Confluence**: Convert and sync Markdown files to Confluence pages
- **Hierarchy Preservation**: Maintain directory structure as page hierarchy
- **Smart Link Conversion**: Automatically convert Markdown links to Confluence page links
- **Configuration-Driven**: Flexible YAML configuration
- **Bidirectional Sync**: Keep local and remote content synchronized

## Requirements

- Java 17 or higher

## Usage

After installation, configure authentication:

For Confluence Cloud:
```
$env:CONFLUENCE_USERNAME = "your-email@example.com"
$env:CONFLUENCE_API_TOKEN = "your-api-token"
```

For Confluence Data Center/Server:
```
$env:CONFLUENCE_PAT = "your-personal-access-token"
```

Then sync your documentation:
```
consync sync /path/to/docs
```

For more information, visit: https://github.com/yourusername/consync
